  [ ] getCart auto-create empty cart (consistent with addItem)
  [ ] Cart item ownership validation on remove/update
  [ ] createCart response — include isActive, timestamps
  [ ] Resolve userId from JWT principal (after Phase 3 Auth)

Learn (completed):
- Transactions, Service Layer, Validation

================================================================================
PHASE 5: ORDER MANAGEMENT (FEATURE_ROADMAP Phase 4)
================================================================================
Status: ⬜ NOT STARTED — after Auth + foundation polish

Schema ready in schema.sql:
  orders       (order_number, status, payment_status, total_amount, address FKs)
  order_items  (quantity, price snapshot)

Flow:
  Add Product → Add To Cart → Checkout → Create Order → Reduce Inventory

Build:
  [ ] OrderEntity, OrderItemEntity
  [ ] OrderStatus enum (CREATED, CONFIRMED, SHIPPED, CANCELLED, etc.)
  [ ] IOrderRepository, IOrderItemRepository
  [ ] OrderService.checkout(userId, shippingAddressId, billingAddressId)
  [ ] OrderController — checkout, list, detail, cancel
  [ ] @Transactional checkout (cart → order, decrement stock, clear cart)
  [ ] OrderNotFoundException, InvalidOrderStateException

Endpoints (planned):
  POST   /orders/checkout
  GET    /orders
  GET    /orders/{orderId}
  PATCH  /orders/{orderId}/cancel

Checkout business rules (@Transactional):
  1. Validate cart not empty
  2. Validate shipping address belongs to user
  3. Re-check stock for every cart item
  4. Create orders row; create order_items with price snapshot
  5. Decrement stock_quantity; clear cart items
  6. Roll back on any failure

Learn:
- @Transactional, ACID, Rollback, Concurrency

